The paper proposes a regularization method for Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to learn compact binary representations of image patches. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training a discriminator network and introducing loss terms, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the resulting binary image descriptors on image matching and retrieval tasks, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
